\begin{align*}
\Delta G &= -16.5\ \text{kJ mol}^{-1} + (8.314 \times 10^{-3}\ \text{kJ K}^{-1}\ \text{mol}^{-1}) \times (298\ \text{K}) \times \ln\left(\frac{16}{3}\right)\\
&= -16.5 + 2.478\ln\left(\frac{16}{3}\right)\\
&\approx -5.61\ \text{kJ mol}^{-1}
\end{align*}

Rounding the result to an integer, we get:

\begin{equation*}
\boxed{-6}\ \text{kJ mol}^{-1}
